properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 12 at 3:39PM EST until February 14 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Winds becoming southerly tonight into Thursday and
increasing to 15 to 20 kt with gusts up to 30 kt, then becoming
west during Thursday. Seas 3 to 6 feet expected.

* WHERE...The southern New Jersey Atlantic coastal waters and the
Delaware Atlantic coastal waters.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Thursday to 6 AM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM THURSDAY TO 6 AM EST FRIDAY
